	<h2>Voter Information</h2>
        <!-- Add your voter information content here -->
        <!-- ... (previous code) ... -->
	In India, citizens become eligible to vote once they turn 18 years old. To exercise this right, individuals need to register as voters. The process of registration involves filling out a form either online or offline, providing necessary identification documents and proof of residence. Once registered, voters receive a Voter ID card, confirming their eligibility to participate in elections.

On the day of voting, registered voters need to visit their assigned polling station. The process begins with verifying one's identity through the Voter ID card. After verification, the voter receives a ballot or uses an Electronic Voting Machine (EVM) to cast their vote in private. The voter then marks their choice, keeping the selection confidential. The vote is then officially cast, contributing to the democratic process. This step-by-step guide ensures that citizens, upon reaching the eligible age, can easily participate in the democratic system by exercising their right to vote.
